<h1>Family Tree</h1>
<p>The family tree feature lets you visually display and manage family relationships.</p>

<h2>Viewing the Family Tree</h2>
<p>Tap the family tree toggle button at the top of the main screen to switch from the age map to the family tree view.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Automatically grouped by generation (Grandparents → Parents → Self → Children → Grandchildren)</li>
  <li>Relationship lines are drawn automatically.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Relationship Types</h2>
<p>You can add relationships from a person's detail screen.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Parent-Child</strong> — Parent and child relationship</li>
  <li><strong>Spouse</strong> — Current or former spouse</li>
  <li><strong>Sibling</strong> — Brother/sister relationship</li>
  <li><strong>Romantic</strong> — Romantic partner</li>
</ul>

<h2>Setting Up Relationships</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Tap a person on the age map to open their details.</li>
  <li>Tap the relationship edit button.</li>
  <li>Select the relationship type and choose the related person.</li>
  <li>Save — the family tree will update automatically.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Editing/Deleting Relationships</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Tap an existing relationship in the person detail screen to change the type or delete it.</li>
  <li>Spouse relationships can be changed between current and former status.</li>
</ul>
